Derangement	#61.	 complicate, involve, perplex, confound
Destruction	#162.	 devour, swallow up, sap, mine, blast, bomb, blow to smithereens, drop the big one, confound
Indiscrimination	#465a.	 overlook a distinction &c. (neglect), confound, confuse. Adj. indiscriminate
Uncertainty	#475.	 confuse, confound
Confutation	#479.	 parry, negative, controvert, rebut, confound, disconfirm, redargue, expose, show the fallacy of, defeat
Success	#731.	 put down, put to flight, put to the rout, put hors de combat [Fr.], put out of court. silence, quell, nonsuit, checkmate, upset, confound, nonplus, stalemate, trump
Wonder	#870.	 stun, stupefy, petrify, confound, bewilder, flabbergast, stagger, throw on one's beam ends, fascinate, turn the head, take away one's breath, strike dumb
